OL,3,CBeavers set to be legally recognised
OL,4,Cas a native species in Wales
OL,6,FShe told the Senedd any potential
OL,7,Fdownsides could be mitigated, arguing
OL,8,Fthat beavers can be managed "easily
OL,9,Fand at relatively low cost" by
OL,10,Flearning from international models.
OL,12,FBut the Labour politician stressed
OL,13,Fthat for the project to succeed,
OL,14,Fbeavers must be given protected
OL,15,Fspecies status and recognised as a
OL,16,Fnative animal.
OL,18,FShe warned that funding for the beaver
OL,19,Fproject comes through the Welsh
OL,20,FGovernment's Nature Networks programme
OL,21,Fwhich ends in March 2026.
